      "content": "Your sense of permanent shame can be overwhelming, but history shows that individuals often endure professional ruin to protect the integrity of their community. Retiring or leaving the field quietly might feel like an escape, yet remaining hidden can be a heavier burden than facing the truth. Please consider speaking with a psychiatrist immediately; they can help you navigate this grief in a way that supports your life, regardless of any past mistakes.",
